---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Is OI a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only — NOT Valid in TWL (2 Points)"
  description="OI is valid in SOWPODS (Collins) but NOT in TWL. Worth only 2 points (O=1, I=1), OI is a British exclamation used to get attention. Check your dictionary before playing."
  keywords="is oi a scrabble word, oi scrabble valid, oi sowpods only, oi british exclamation, oi two letter word scrabble, oi not valid twl"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Is OI a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only — NOT Valid in TWL (2 Points)",
    "description": "OI is valid in SOWPODS (Collins) but NOT in TWL. Worth 2 points, it's a British exclamation to get someone's attention.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-29",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-oi-a-scrabble-word" }
  })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is OI a valid Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "OI is valid ONLY in SOWPODS (Collins Scrabble Words). It is NOT valid in TWL (Tournament Word List) used in North American NASPA-sanctioned play." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many points is OI worth in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "OI is worth just 2 points: O(1) + I(1) = 2. It's one of the lowest-scoring two-letter words in the game, but useful for vowel dumping and parallel plays." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What does OI mean?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "OI is a British/Australian exclamation used to attract attention, similar to 'Hey!' It's commonly used in informal speech: 'Oi! Over here!'" } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Two-Letter Words</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is OI a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only — NOT Valid in TWL</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>3 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">OI — that distinctly British shout to get someone's attention — is one of those two-letter plays that can catch North American players off guard. Valid in SOWPODS for international play but absent from TWL, this humble 2-point word is mainly useful for vowel dumping and tight parallel formations.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-orange-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-orange-950/30 to-amber-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-orange-500/70">⚠ SOWPODS Only</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">OI</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-orange-300 font-semibold mb-3">2 points · O(1) + I(1) · British exclamation · SOWPODS only</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">OI is valid in Collins (international) but INVALID in TWL (North America). At just 2 points, it's purely a tactical play — dump vowels or create parallel cross-words in SOWPODS games.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-orange-500/30 bg-orange-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-orange-400">2</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-red-400">✗</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Invalid TWL</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">✓</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid SOWPODS</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-orange-400">8+8</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">O + I Tiles in Bag</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">What Does OI Mean?</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">📖 Definition</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">OI is a <span class="text-white font-medium">British and Australian exclamation used to attract attention</span>, similar to "Hey!" in American English. It's informal and direct — "Oi! Over here!" — and is deeply embedded in British working-class culture and Australian slang.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Dictionary Status</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10"><p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ INVALID in TWL (NASPA)</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Not in Tournament Word List. Playing OI in North American tournaments results in a challenge loss. NASPA considers it too informal and regionally specific.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Valid in SOWPODS (Collins)</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Accepted in Collins Scrabble Words. Legal in international tournaments, UK/Australian clubs, and Collins-based online games.</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategic Uses</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Vowel dump:</span> Stuck with too many vowels? OI uses two common vowels at once, clearing rack space for better tiles in your next draw.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Parallel plays:</span> Both O and I are incredibly common on boards. OI fits into parallel formations where each letter forms cross-words with existing tiles for bonus points.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Better alternatives:</span> OI scores only 2pts. Consider OX(9), OI's SOWPODS cousin ZO(11), or universally valid OE(2) which works in TWL too.</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Other SOWPODS-Only 2-Letter Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-orange-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OI</span><span class="text-orange-400 text-xs">2pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-orange-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">EW</span><span class="text-orange-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-orange-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">YA</span><span class="text-orange-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-orange-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ZE</span><span class="text-orange-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-orange-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CH</span><span class="text-orange-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-orange-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">KY</span><span class="text-orange-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-ya-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is YA a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/is-ew-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is EW a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word's validity instantly — free, realtime, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
